content: Probably one of the most interesting things on the play store to do with android. I found this looking for a virtual lab during the cold 19 shut down, I'm bored to death. The game? It's sort of a game I guess, as there is an end, it's still more like a digital forensics lab without any industry standard tools, or anything real difficult. Was still fun, I kinda hope that maybe you might do one more challenging like make it where we have to get a dump off a device, make it like a capture the flag.
I somehow finished the game in five minutes??
Exceptional!
Great game

[Spoliers] I'll be real honest here, I usually don't write reviews but man this game did something to me. This game made me realize that I was a domestic absuser and after diving in depth into the story and really seeing how my actions can affect someone so harshly it made me take a look in the mirror. I'm now attending therapy for my problems, but if I had to say something to the devolpers I'd say thank you. This game is a real eye opener to a very real and serious issue.
I bought this game and I'm stuck! I have no idea what I'm doing because it tells me NOTHING! Lol I love a challenge 😜 so that's why I gave 4 stars.
Was pretty good. I needed more direction and had to look up tips.
Loved it.

This is a gem in a sea of trash on the mobile market. Although relatively short you definitely get enough enjoyment from the game, as it isn't very pricey. If you have a little bit of a mind for puzzling you will spend about 2 hours playing this game. Without spoiling anything, the game gives you an excellent example of the subject matter.
Awesome game!! Definitely worth it. Great storyline. Not too long or too short.

This is emotional and intense, and I wish this type of game was more well-known. This story shines a light on such a normalized and grim type of abusive relationship, and I truly do wish that someone who is in such a relationship but doesn't know it yet, gets to play through this and realize that they can leave to somewhere safe.

Not really a gamer but I was bored this weekend, so I figured I'd give this app a shot.. I must say that I was immediately immersed with the story as if it was a real person. It's fun and engaging. But be prepared to do a lot of reading.
Great story, with well built characters, nice puzzles and, more importantly, a great lesson and actual useful help on relationships
This was amazing! The game made me FEEL things, which doesn't happen often. Totally worth it
Took about a day. But it was a great ride.
Great game! But short :(
Brilliant idea and good execution. Only issue is that it was a tad short. But few games have impacted me like this!

I... Am astounded. And a little disturbed. ***POTENTIAL SPOILER ALERT BELOW*** . . . . . . I think I may have been in the same kind of situation. I realised as I read some of the info. I'm fine now but...it was heartbreaking for Past Me.
Every bit as delightful as the last one. Another great, unique puzzle game with a lovely story.

Another wicked, intriguing and elaborate, enticing story. Fun intuitive design with complexity too. Enjoyable narrative and well written. Short but it still manages to pace itself and keep your attention. Wicked job, everyone!! Can't wait to enjoy more content 😊
Good. Finished in 1 or 2 hours. Kinda good.

Took a couple of leaps to work out some of the passwords but a really investing story that made me want to keep digging and work out what happened. Bought during a sale and fairly short, but something I'll definitely reccomend to my friends to experience.

At this point how games like this one work shouldn't be unfamiliar; you're either in it for the story, or you shouldn't play this. Like the last one, this has a compelling story. Unlike the last, what's going on is pretty obvious from the start - but it's still fun. 2-3 hours, maybe, to complete. I'd recommend it.
Keeps crashing
Loved it, different but very well enjoyed the game.
Very good game highly recommend!
These are the type of games I want more of.

It's not totally rubbish, but very short - about 3hrs to complete. Most of the time is spent just reading messages and emails, with just a few tasks needing codes to unlock more text. A fair enough narrative, but game costs too much for such a short time.

I absolutely loved this! Such a deep, immersive story. It had puzzles, romance, drama, excitement, suspense...it really felt like I was legitimately holding someone's phone and actually doing everything. The way the app fills the screen, and looks realistic, adds to the thrill. Please, make more!!
Don't miss this one.
Pretty intense emotional impact. I really felt protective of the main character. Very immersive.
Not bad..I liked the concept..
I liked the previous one more since its resolution felt more freeing. The end of this story flips between preachy edu-tainment and being a downer. Otherwise very well made.
It's so great overall!! I like this a lot! Thanks for making this <3

The game was way to short it wasn't a full experience of a lost phone usually with a lost phone games you have to search for alot of clues and search for the person who went missing this was just way to short of a missing phone game I don't recommend this game
I Definitely enjoyed this game, it was piecing everything. I would love to see more of these, but to go further in depth. More files on the phone to go through. :)
Great and enjoyable game!
I cannot recommend this game enough. Not only is the interface immersive and fun to use, the puzzles are great and encourage you to engage with the story. Oh, the story. This is so excellent.

Amazing. This game and the first one, "A Normal Lost Phone", both bring attention and insight to some very real and important human experiences that need to be better understood by humankind at large. The existence of these games is so valuable and they both left me sobbing.
So clever and powerful. Everyone should play this game.
Amazing way to tell a story. Not only does it touch a really important and delicate subject, it does it in a magnificent way. I want more games like this.
Simply Amazing. Puzzles are reasonably challenging and the story is very well developed.
Hit scarily close to home. Accurate and atmospheric.

So... It don't take like 2 weeks or really long time downloaded it about 1 hour ago and finished it really quick but it's really interesting you really try to figure it out and it's really good for your brain because the answer is not open written you really need to check everything and take note and picure it all toghter to get to the end of it... I recommend doing it without cheating... It get more exciting the more you get into it tho...

This Game was fun as hell.The story of the game tells is so intriguing and the mystery behind everything is fun to solve. If you have a short attention span this may not be a game for you but if your really interested in the mystery of it all I would highly recommend this game.
Love the story.
Amazing concept, brilliant and hard-hitting storyline!
Short but engrossing, the dialogue was well written and realistic and I found myself wrapped up in the story even though there wasn't a huge amount of mystery or any crazy twists.
Again, a moving and touching game. Well done.
Amazing and upsetting and the same time.
This was a lot harder than the other one. But boy, very satisfying when done. This ended better than the previous game.
Just like the original, it has a great story and it is worth the time and money to play. I hope another one is in the works.
Good story. Hard and heavy at times, but worth the time and money.
Wow! It was a great experience! Thank you for makung such a great game!

Pro Tip: get a sheet of paper or some physical writing piece and just note down everything important. Review: Great game, just as the first in the Lost Phone series! For the next one I would suggest adding night mode, so that this game can be easily played at night without straining the eyes. scalable text size would be a great accessibility feature I'd love to see! Thank you so much for such an important life experience (it's not just a game) - I'll definitely recommend Laura's Story as well!
The game itself is really nice bases on domestic violence. Reading through text I feels like a Novela, really good. I got stuck a bit but at the end the game was short but at the end is a must buy.
It's a great game that really opens up your eyes to how psychological abuse takes place. I would love to see a game with a theme focused on assault on men and other such issues
A clever and compassionate game.
Great sequel to the original game. Interesting (but sad) story.

Big trigger warning for relationship abuse. They do a good job making you slowly unfold Laura's life and puzzle out passwords to get new details. I haven't completed the game, but I don't want to relive Laura's story anymore. The details and mechanics of this game are too immersive for someone coping with PTSD.

Absolutely heartbreaking but truly wonderful and has an important message. All the puzzles were fun and interesting, and presenting this game as exploring a stranger's lost phone is such a cool and immersive way to go about this!

Please make more games like this!! This game is literally perfect. Everything I want in a game is in this game. Storytelling is top notch and it makes you feel so involved in the story and characters. Love it!! I request one lost phone game per month minimum kay? Thanks! Lol
Amazing. 👏 Same as the first game, great story telling, such a good message for everyone out there that are or had experience this. Keep up the good work and looking forward for more.
An excellent interactive game with a complex story.
Finished the game in one sitting. It is amazing!
good game. would have been nice to have more content

This, similar to Sam's story is a really powerful message about an issue many face. I found the puzzles to be a bit trickier this time which is great! This story really hit hard for me as I'm sure it has for many. The visuals and writing was nice and unlike a lot of dialouge this didn't feel forced. I really liked this game as well, thank you game devs. I really enjoyed it 💕
I did not expect that story! Just like the first game, it had a good twist that thankfully ended on a positive note. But wow!
too short and very rushed story. a ridiculous bunch of story progress after each action. only 3 or 4 easy puzzles to solve. SIMULACRA IS A FAR SUPERIOR GAME
engaging story, drops you right in and makes you explore the phone for clues on how to proceed
I really enjoyed the game but it is far to short, finished it in 1 hour. please release some more games but maybe make them last a couple of days to feel real 😌😊 x
Pretty good. Story is short.
Well written game. I got stuck a couple of times, but I don't think it was too difficult.
Interesting concept and story on the first playthrough. But I can't trigger the "No trail left behind" achievement for some reason.

great game. i wish there was more visual amd audio to it, like simulacra or sara is missing. also, at the end it said i missed two goals but wont tell me what they were. even tho i think i got them all. at least all that were listed
I'm glad I didn't look up the answers to the puzzles. This game handles an interesting story in a great way. I don't play mobile games often but I highly recommend this one. (You may need a notepad!)

Excellent use of the medium and the form. Interesting and relevant topic. The "puzzles" are sometimes frustrating, and the narration gets heavy handed towards the end, but this is a lovely experiment that's worth exploring.
Nice little phone sim game. Good story, nice interface
Love it make more
Fantastic game. Hungry for a third entry in the series!

I enjoyed both the puzzles and the execution of the story. True to life and 
informative.

I'm a little conflicted about this game. On the one hand, the theme is an 
important one and it really is conveyed in an interesting manner, but it's 
nothing new, because they did the same thing with "A Normal Lost Phone". 
The story is engaging and pieces together nicely, but the outcome is 
foreseeable while reading the first few messages. And the gameplay is good, 
but it lacks a few features I would have liked it to have, like being able 
to search through conversations for information or just copying and pasting 
things. So all in all, as a game, I gave it three stars, but it's really 
worth playing it, if only for the subject matter it is dealing with.
Is that it? Nice game but to short

Excellent little narrative puzzler. Especially good to indulge your 
snooping desires.
Great story! I loved all the puzzles to get behind what happened

This game is really good! Some of the riddles are a bit challenging though, 
I had to research two or three. Also I finished it in one day! That's OK 
though, because I will play it again for sure.
Excellent story and puzzle fusion

This is a really good story and good characters guys seriously download 
this and a important message in the game

This game was boring and pointless I can't believe I wasted my money on 
this garbage.
Amazing game that teaches about emotional abuse and domestic violence.
Both terrifying and interesting game, a must play

This really is a temendous story telling medium. The puzzles are clever and 
well thought out. (Apart from the final puzzle - which is almost impossible 
without looking up the answer!) I want another one of these games. Two is 
not enough! Give me a third game! Please and thank you.
A great game about another important issue, with a much more thoughtful approach to the ending than the previous game.
Short story, no replay value, unlike other lost phone apps like Simulacra. Not worth the money for me. But good efforts.
Just ok
It's crazy how much lives change at the drop of a hat.... hug someone you love tonught.
A good mystery sequel to A Normal Lost Phone, I liked the first games' soundtrack better though.
Good
It was a really great experience to play this game. Really recommended it to everyone!
Eye-opening, realistic scenario. I wish it would have been made earlier.

Controls are easy, finished this game in a day. Very few puzzles but content wise it is great and it has a good message- something I hope everyone else will take lesson from. I'd just like to chime in on mental abuse with long distance relationship. It doesn't have to be a romantic one and it will be harder to spot and even harder to tell, simply because online relationships are taken less seriously. Victims are even more ashamed to tell about it because it is "less real" but it can happen and it will look normal. I hope the team will be able to tackle this if they ever choose to make another one to the series.

This is an amazing game and a very needed message too to make there should be more games like this it was so well made u have personally been in the same situation and feel this game gives more awareness so thank you xx
Game is very easy and simple really regret paying for it
Very well written. Less involved than the previous Lost Phone game, but just as engaging!

Can I have my money back please? Puzzles are simple or very simple. And simple to the rate they are not interesring.  Font is so small that it makes my eyes scream and cry to stop. And the whole racism and misogyny of the game (the bad guy is "that damn white male", of course) make this thing just disgusting.
Fantastic! I'm really glad someone finally decided to create a game about abusive relationships awareness. Thank you so much for having such idea, this is just amazing
Great game. Good storyline...it unfolded slowly and was engaging.
To hard I could not play with out needing a walkthrough to help.
It seemed a little short, but it was an interesting and imaginative game
Warning, the game deals with abuse. But this is a game that portrays abuse really well. The game has great writing. And it's short, but good.

I like the concept of this game. It sets a very mysterious tone to the main character and makes you wonder what is going on in their life. The game also shows the player a different perspective on digital communication which I found interesting. However, the more you are sent through the many different apps and email clients, the more tedious this game becomes. There are times where you have to memorize a very long passcode (no, you can't copy and paste it). Or times where you can't tell if this weird anime-style portrait of this person is the same person or not. Or times where you want to scroll through text but are limited to scrolling at an extremely slow pace. There are many little things like these that made me stop playing this game and it further upset me after realizing I've spent the past hour running in circles because of how terribly crappy this person's phone is. 6/10.
Eerie and entertaining!
Another utterly incredibly told narrative experience - cannot recommend enough, although you may be want to be aware of the general subject matter

some parts of the story need to be smoothed out. it would be better to insert little signs/red flags of whats going on earlier in the story. it felt rather heavy handed at the very end. this topic is very sensitive but most situations involving this issue start subtle and ramp up at the end. the delivery leaves much to be desired.
Good story but not work the money

Beautiful! Once again, Playdius have made an impactful and poignant story about a topic that deserves more attention. They've handled it with respect and thought. The game was a bit short (it felt a bit shorter than A Normal Lost Phone?), but it was great nonetheless.
Sadly very relevant to me. These stories need to be told, its a long journey to recognising what's happening to you and getting out safely is crucial. The game brings light to a very serious issue.
This is the best game I've played in a long time!  Imaginative, fun, engaging!  Fantastic!
After playing the first games, Another Lost phone is very compact, it tells a story elegantly and you feel like a real detective playing it. I learned a lot!
Mature narrative about abusive relationships, with smart use of the phone interface to make clever riddles. Quite original and appealing.

I heard about this game from Dodger on The Cooptional Podcast. Glad I checked it out. Very compelling story and told in such a unique way. I read every sms, email, note, etc. I also love how you progress through the game. Great work! Can't wait to check out the previous title.
Important subject but bad as a game. Short, spoiled already on the front page, inconsequential gameplay
It's another lost phone (game) And it's great
Please keep making these games!

Ironically, I have a project I chose to do on domestic violence and this game helped put some things in perspective. This provides a good insight on the lives of people dealing with this problem, hopefully it sheds light to those that need it.
This is another lost phone, simple enough. You got to use clues to solve the story of about what happened to Laura by digging up information on the phone.
Loved it. Short but thrilling

This game is yet another lost phone type game, where you take control of another person's phone. Its driven by an emotional narrative, and one that I think many people can relate to. I recommend this game to anyone in any sort of relationship, so you can understand the warning sings of domestic violence.
Not worth the money
A beautifully designed game with an amazing story that makes you won't to need put it down.
The previous game was a better story to tell, but both games were a great piece of story telling

Content Warning: This game deals heavily with abusive relationships. It's handled well though! Really compelling and thought-provoking story! A few moments were less emersive than A Normal Lost Phone but besides that I loved it!
Fantastic game!
Nice, but not enough new mechanics for a sequel.

Awesome game. Every bit as good as the first one. Felt a tad short but it could just be cuz I knew how to navigate better as I had already beaten the first one. Either way I'd say it's worth the time and money.

If you've played A Normal Lost Phone you'll know what to expect here. The writing is great and it really feels like you're exploring someone's phone. It's a little shorter then I'd have liked (shorter than the first I think) but wonderfully crafted.

Crafted game design and catching story that kept me glued to my phone for about 3 hours investigating, guessing, connecting loose ends to progress and questioning everything and everyone till the end. A very important, too often seen and way too ignored topic in our societies that made me look around and think twice. Beautifully designed interface and graphics, nice to see, not tiring for the eyes, easy and smooth navigation and an original soundtrack that sets the tone for the perfect atmosphere to enjoy the experience this game offers. 5*!!!
Important game. Good narrative and good gameplay
Amazing story, just like the first

I loved it. Not only did the writing and interactivity make it an incredibly engaging experience, but it deals with extremely important issues that many people go through without even realizing it. I only wish the game were longer.
After playing the first game, I knew I had to get this one, the story is real and captivating, and it felt so realistic that it just blew me away. Another great game by Plug in digital.
While I totally loved A Normal Lost Phone its successor didn't really touch me. I can't exactly tell what is missing, but it is missing the 'spirit' its presuccessor had.
Another gorgeous game with entertaining puzzles and a captivating story. I absolutely recommend you play it (also the developers are super nice people <3)
The game is both fun, interesting and raise awareness about real important issues. Only complaint is that it ended so fast ;)
